<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Lakers Sign Top Draft Pick </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- The Los Angeles Lakers signed  
first-round draft choice Devean George and free agents Gerald 
Jordan and Garry Garrett on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	No terms were announced, but as the 23rd overall selection in  
the NBA draft three months ago, George is eligible for a three-year 
contract for $2.1 million, not including a signing bonus. 
</P>
<P>
	George, a 6-foot-8 swingman, averaged 23.5 points and 9.0  
rebounds in four years at Augsburg (Minn.) College. 
</P>
<P>
	Jordan, a 6-10 forward-center, played at Pittsburgh from  
1995-97, and then spent one season playing in Cyprus, averaging 
19.0 points and 18.6 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Garrett, a 6-4 guard, played at San Diego State from 1996-98.  
</P>
<P>
	The Lakers begin training camp Tuesday at UC Santa Barbara,  
where they will practice until opening the exhibition season on 
Oct. 12 against the Washington Wizards at Little Rock, Ark. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
