<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bills Lead Dolphins 13-9 at Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Linebacker John Holecek forced Dan Marino to fumble  
and Gabe Northern returned it 59 yards for the game's first 
touchdown, giving the Buffalo Bills a 13-9 lead over the Miami 
Dolphins at halftime Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
	After forcing Buffalo to punt from its own end zone, the  
Dolphins took over at the Bills' 40-yard line. But on third-and-4, 
Holecek hit Marino from the blind side, the first time he was 
sacked this season, forcing the fumble. 
</P>
<P>
	Northern scooped it up, broke one tackle, then rambled untouched  
for the score. 
</P>
<P>
	Marino was 14-of-25 for 181 yards in the half and Olindo Mare  
kicked three field goals, including one on the final play of the 
second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Marino, running the Dolphins 2-minute offense, connected with  
Oronde Gadsden for a 36-yard gain. He hit four of his next five 
passes to set up Mare's third field goal, a 26-yarder. 
</P>
<P>
	Gadsden caught three passes for 46 yards, and O.J. McDuffie  
added four receptions in the half for 46 yards. 
</P>
<P>
	Buffalo got on the scoreboard first, driving 51 yards to the  
Miami 9 to set up a 26-yard field goal by Steve Christie. Though 
the Dolphins punted on their first two possessions, they used a 
turnover, the first of the game, to even the score. 
</P>
<P>
	Buffalo quarterback Doug Flutie fumbled a snap, and safety Shawn  
Wooden recovered it on the Bills' 41. Miami drove 28 yards, most of 
which came on the ensuing play when Marino hit fullback Rob Konrad 
for a 25-yard gain. 
</P>
<P>
	Mare's 30-yard field goal tied the game.  
</P>
<P>
	After a seven play, 35-yard drive, Mare hit a 44-yarder to give  
the Dolphins their first lead of the night. 
</P>
<P>
	Flutie was 3-of-7 for 71 yards in the first quarter, but missed  
on all five passes in the second quarter. He added a 17-yard 
scramble. 
</P>
<P>
	The Bills entered the game with a 2-1 record. The Dolphins were  
2-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
