<HEADLINE> Search On for 3-Year-Old in Colo. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT COLLINS, Colo. (AP) -- About 40 people were searching on  
Monday for a 3-year-old boy who had disappeared two days earlier 
while hiking with family and friends. Fear for his safety was 
growing by the hour. 
</P>
<P>
	Jaryd Atadero of Littleton was walking in between two groups of  
relatives and friends in Poudre Canyon on Saturday afternoon when 
he vanished. The boy's parents were not on the hike. 
</P>
<P>
	The terrain is so rocky that search dogs have to wear pads on  
their feet, said Larimer County sheriff's deputy Cindy Gordon. 
Divers have searched the Poudre River several times. 
</P>
<P>
	``Time is essential,'' Ms. Gordon said.  
</P>
<P>
	Jaryd was wearing clothes warm enough to get him through the  
freezing temperatures of Saturday and Sunday nights. Higher 
temperatures, with lows in the low 40s, were forecast for Monday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
	On Sunday, an Air Force helicopter crashed as it was carrying  
rescuers on the search for Jaryd. Five people on board suffered 
minor injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	A private company provided a search helicopter Monday afternoon.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
