<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Union Shuts Out D'Backs' Miller </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MESA, Ariz. (AP) -- While Arizona's Damian Miller plays on a  
division champion, you won't see his name or signature on the 
merchandise. 
</P>
<P>
	Miller broke ranks with the players' association during the  
1994-95 strike, participating with replacement players during 
spring training in February-March 1995. However, he insists he 
wasn't a replacement player because he never joined them in actual 
spring training games. 
</P>
<P>
	The players' association has refused membership to all players  
who it views as replacements. As a result, he doesn't receive 
licensing money from the union, which usually amounts to 
$50,000-$100,000 annually. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
