<HEADLINE> Cavaliers Sign Five Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- A.J. Bramlett, the Cleveland Cavaliers'  
second-round draft pick, signed with the team along with four other 
players on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Bramlett, a 6-foot-10 forward, played four seasons at the  
University of Arizona and finished as the Wildcates' sixth leading 
career rebounder (817). He averaged 14.2 points and 9.4 rebounds 
his senior year. 
</P>
<P>
	The Cavaliers also signed 5-foot-5 guard Earl Boykins, who  
played in 22 games for Cleveland and the New Jersey Jets last year, 
averaging 3.0 points per game. 
</P>
<P>
	Also signed were center Matt Fish, who averaged 3.5 points in 50  
career games with five NBA teams; Tony Smith, an eight-year NBA 
veteran who averaged 5.5 points in his career; and Jamel Thomas, a 
6-foot-6 forward who finished as the third-leading career scorer at 
Providence with 1,971 points. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
