<HEADLINE> Welsh Rugby Union Suspends Tix Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CARDIFF, Wales (AP) -- The Welsh Rugby Union, host of the 1999  
World Cup, has suspended ticket manager Richard Wright following a 
ticketing mixup at the opening ceremony and game between Wales and 
Argentina at Millennium Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
	Already under fire because overdue completion of the new  
72,500-seat capacity stadium overshadowed the tournament buildup, 
the Union's troubles escalated when it developed that tickets for 
some seats last Friday had been duplicated while 200 vacant seats 
had never been sold. 
</P>
<P>
	It was uncertain whether the problem was caused by technical or  
human error, but with tickets for this weekend's game already 
allocated, there was no guarantee the same problem wouldn't occur 
again. 
</P>
<P>
	The empty seats were reallocated to people queuing in the  
stadium ticket office after the opening ceremony began. 
  	   	
</P>
