</P>
<P>
	The Burlington, Mass.- based developer of multimedia-conference  
software said it expects to lose money and fall short of earnings 
forecasts. Ezenia, which until last month was named VideoServer, 
blamed lower demand for some of its products. 

</P>
<P>
	Harleysville Group, down 1 1/2 at 13 3/4  
</P>
<P>
	The Harleysville, Pa.-based regional insurance holding company  
said claims from Hurricane Floyd, higher-than- expected payments on 
commercial policies and other costs caused it to lose money in the 
third quarter. 

</P>
<P>
	Incyte Pharmaceuticals, down 6 19/32 at 16 3/4  
</P>
<P>
	The Palo Alto, Calif.-based provider of genetic information to  
drugmakers said it expects third-quarter sales to be lower than 
expected due to delays in new agreements and contracts. 




  	   	
