<HEADLINE> Many in U.S. Say Y2K No Big Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- It happens only once every thousand years, but  
most Americans think the coming of the new millennium will be just 
another new year. 
</P>
<P>
	An ABC News poll suggests that six out of 10 think this is a new  
year like any other and one out of 10 won't even stay up to see the 
new millennium arrive. 
</P>
<P>
	Two-thirds of those polled say they don't usually go out on New  
Year's Eve. Just over half, 54 percent, say they don't plan to go 
out this year, while 38 percent say they will. Three out of four 
say they've made no plans yet for New Year's Eve. 
</P>
<P>
	The ABC poll of 506 adults was taken Aug. 16-22 and has an error  
margin of plus or minus 4.5 percentage points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
