<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NYC Cardinal Says Tumor Not Cancer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Cardinal John O'Connor said Monday that the  
brain tumor he had removed is not considered cancerous. 
</P>
<P>
	Asked if doctors are using the word ``cancer'' to describe his  
case, O'Connor said: ``No one has used it. ... I haven't been using 
it. They told me I had a brain tumor. They took it out. And now 
they're using the X-ray treatment to assure there's nothing else.'' 
</P>
<P>
	O'Connor's forehead is bright red from the radiation he is  
receiving. 
</P>
<P>
	``Each morning I go for five minutes and they zap me on either  
side of the head with X-rays,'' he said. His treatment is scheduled 
to continue for a few more weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Connor, 79, spoke about his condition after blessing a new  
cancer treatment facility affiliated with St. Vincent's Medical 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Connor was released from Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer  
Center about a month ago. Doctors removed a tumor from the surface 
of his brain during the 11 days he was hospitalized. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
