<HEADLINE> AL Umpires Picked for First Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Jim McKean and Joe Brinkman were picked as crew  
chiefs Monday for the first round of the AL playoffs, and Rick Reed 
was chosen for the AL championship series. 
</P>
<P>
	The crew that opens in New York on Tuesday night for the  
Rangers-Yankees series has Jim Joyce behind the plate, Chuck 
Meriwether at first, Tim Welke at second, McKean at third, John 
Shulock in left field and Durwood Merrill in right. 
</P>
<P>
	That crew switches to the Red Sox-Indians for Games 3-4, then  
returns to the Rangers-Yankees if a fifth game is necessary. 
</P>
<P>
	For Wednesday's opener in Cleveland, the umpires will be Rocky  
Roe behind the plate, Larry Young at first, John Hirschbeck at 
second, Brinkman at third, Mike Reilly in left and Derryl Cousins 
in right. 
</P>
<P>
	For the league championship, Tim McClelland opens behind the  
plate with Dan Morrison at first, Reed at second, Al Clark at 
third, Dale Scott in left and Tim Tschida in right. 
</P>
<P>
	In a survey by players last year, McClelland was the AL's  
top-rated ump, followed by Joyce. Hirschbeck was fourth, Reilly 
fifth, Tschida eighth, Scott ninth, Welke 10th, McKean 12th, Roe 
13th, Reed 14th, Morrison 17th, Cousins 18th, Shulock 21st, Young 
22nd, Clark 25th, Meriwether 26th and Brinkman 29th. 
</P>
<P>
	Merrill, who is retiring after this season, was 31st, which was  
next to last. 
  	   	
</P>
