<HEADLINE> Graham Has Surgery for Clot Removal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GAINESVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Freshman Earnest Graham, Florida's  
leading rusher this year, underwent surgery Monday to remove a 
blood clot from his left thigh. 
</P>
<P>
	Graham suffered a severe thigh bruise in a victory against  
Kentucky on Sept. 25. Doctors say they will review his status next 
week and determine when he can return. 
</P>
<P>
	Graham rushed for 311 yards in three-plus games before suffering  
the injury. He joins receiver Travis Taylor (ankle) and center Zac 
Zedalis (knee) as key Florida players being held out due to 
injuries. 
  	   	
