<DOCNO> APW19991004.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-04 22:20:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dean Convicted of Sex With Student </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MARION, Ark. (AP) -- A former high school administrator has been  
convicted of having sex with a cheerleader after offering to take 
her home to retrieve her heart medicine. 
</P>
<P>
	Wally Love, 41, was sentenced Monday to three years in prison,  
the minimum sentence. He faced up to 10 years after being found 
guilty of violating a minor. 
</P>
<P>
	Love's only comment after his sentence was, ``God is good. He is  
good all the time.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The alleged victim, now 19, said she felt sick at West Memphis  
High School one day in 1997 but had left her heart medicine at 
home. Her mother wasn't home, and Love, then the dean of students, 
told her he'd take her to get her medicine, she said. 
</P>
<P>
	She said he took her to an apartment under the guise of running  
an errand and attacked her. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl, now 19, and her mother shrieked when the verdict was  
read. Her mother cradled the girl in her arms and rocked her as 
proceedings continued. 
</P>
<P>
	As the jury deliberated the sentence, the victim said, ``I want  
him to go to jail. He has to be punished for what he did to me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Love did not put on a defense during the trial, His lawyer,  
Samuel Perkins, said the victim fabricated the story to support a 
lawsuit against Love. 
</P>
<P>
	``They've got this all fixed up,'' Perkins said. ``This is a $2  
million story here.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Love was hired this summer as a junior-high boys and girls coach  
and a special education teacher in a district about an hour from 
West Memphis. However, he took a leave from the new job after 
parents complained. 
</P>
<P>
	Administrators there said they were waiting for this case to end  
before deciding on Love's employment. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
