<HEADLINE> Reagan License Plates OK'd </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Saluting Ronald Reagan as a gifted leader,  
the governor signed a law Monday that will create license plates 
bearing a picture of the former president and California governor. 
</P>
<P>
	Former first lady Nancy Reagan looked on during the ceremony at  
the Ronald Reagan State Building. 
</P>
<P>
	``He took this country to new frontiers of human freedom,'' Gov.  
Gray Davis said, standing in front of a poster-size personalized 
license plate reading ``GIPPER.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``In the early '80s, when the country was wracked with  
self-doubt after Vietnam and Watergate, he taught us to believe in 
ourselves again,'' said Davis, a Democrat. ``And more than anything 
else he restored confidence in America and reasserted patriotism as 
a true American value.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Sales of the Ronald Reagan Presidential Foundation License Plate  
will benefit educational and historical programs at the Ronald 
Reagan Presidential Library in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
	The plates, which will now be designed, will cost an extra $50  
initially and then $40 annually after that. 
  	   	
</P>
