<HEADLINE> Man Charged in Freezer Bodies Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- A man who confessed to killing his wife and  
infant son and hiding their bodies in a freezer was charged with 
two counts of murder Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutor Scott Newman said he hasn't decided whether to seek  
the death penalty against John K. Adams, 24. 
</P>
<P>
	Adams has given interviews in which he admitted to shooting his  
wife, Robin Schafer-Adams, 24, and torturing and killing the 
couple's son, John Ramseys Adams. He wanted to leave his wife after 
meeting another woman, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Adams said he tried several ways to kill his 6-month-old son  
before putting him in a plastic bag and placing him in a freezer 
with the corpse of his mother. An autopsy showed the boy died from 
asphyxiation. 
</P>
<P>
	Police found the frozen bodies wrapped in blue plastic tarps  
bound with duct tape Sept. 22 when a sheriff's detective tried to 
serve Adams with an arrest warrant. Adams was wanted in connection 
with two restaurant holdups. 
</P>
<P>
	Adams eluded police for a week until he was captured Friday near  
Kansas City, Mo. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
