<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 'Mansion Madam' Pleads Guilty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MORRISTOWN, N.J. (AP) -- A woman who ran a brothel in her upscale  
suburban mansion admitted Monday to charging men $200 an hour for 
sex while her fiance stood guard. 
</P>
<P>
	Judith Kelly Dempsey, dubbed the Mansion Madam, pleaded guilty  
to prostitution and violating a probation sentence she received in 
May for running the ``Afternoon Delight'' prostitution service out 
of her Victorian mansion. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors say Dempsey prostituted herself at a Howard Johnson  
motel in August while her fiance, Edwin Accini, served as a lookout 
outside the motel room. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was in her best interest to enter the plea today,'' her  
lawyer, Michael Ascher said. ``It's that simple.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Dempsey said she had turned to prostitution so Accini could pay  
legal fees to cover a custody battle with his ex-wife over their 
daughter. 
</P>
<P>
	Dempsey agreed Monday to give up her Lincoln Town Car, the lease  
to her Jaguar and the $4,847 in cash seized while she was arrested. 
She faces up to three years in prison at her sentencing on Nov. 12. 
</P>
<P>
	She was sentenced in May to three years probation after  
admitting running ``Afternoon Delight.'' Prosecutors say the posh 
bordello catered to well-paid businessmen, many who worked at 
nearby office parks. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
