<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Young's Playing Status Unknown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SANTA CLARA, Calif. (AP) -- Steve Young, sidelined by his fourth  
concussion in three years, underwent a series of tests Monday and 
will visit with his neurologist Tuesday to try to decide whether he 
can resume playing this week. 
</P>
<P>
	Even if Stanford neurosurgeon Dr. Gary Steinberg clears Young to  
return, San Francisco 49ers coach Steve Mariucci left open the 
possibility of holding the quarterback out for another week as a 
precaution and again starting Jeff Garcia. 
</P>
<P>
	Garcia made his first NFL start Sunday in place of the injured  
Young and led the 49ers to a 24-22 victory over the previously 
unbeaten Tennessee Titans. He said he's approaching this Sunday's 
game as if he's going to start. 
</P>
<P>
	``That's the way I approach every week, as far as being mentally  
prepared,'' Garcia said. ``Obviously, listening to the radio or 
reading the newspaper, I would have to think that right now, we 
would be leaning toward me starting. But nothing has been 
determined yet, so I'll just allow them to make that decision.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Young, who watched Sunday's game in street clothes from the  
sideline, said he would like to start playing again but is leaving 
it in the hands of his doctor and coaches. 
</P>
<P>
	``My intent is to try to get healthy for this week,'' said  
Young, who sustained his latest concussion during last Monday 
night's 24-10 win at Arizona. ``It's just going to have to unfold. 
We'll see.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mariucci said a decision on the starting quarterback for  
Sunday's game at St. Louis would be made by Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	``It will be based on what's learned from the tests and his  
visit with the doctor,'' Mariucci said. ``All I can tell you right 
now is it's up in the air.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mariucci conceded there is some concern about allowing Young to  
return for a game being played on the TWA Dome's artificial 
surface, which is harder and less giving than grass. There is also 
Young's history of concussions to consider and the fear he could be 
one more serious hit from being forced into retirement. 
</P>
<P>
	Young already has told his coach he wants to resume playing but  
Mariucci said his decision will be guided by health factors above 
all else. The fact that Garcia also played a sterling game in 
relief of Young has no bearing on the matter. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's a piece of work. He wants to play. I'm not telling you  
anything you don't know, but we're going to make a wise decision 
and do what's best,'' Mariucci said of Young. 
</P>
<P>
	``If Steve is not ready to go, I don't care if we don't have a  
quarterback on the team he's not going to go. It's nice that Jeff 
played a good game but he's not going to play if he's not ready to 
go.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
