<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Warriors Sign Free Agent Legler </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Free agent guard Tim Legler signed a  
one-year contract with the Golden State Warriors on Monday. Terms 
of the deal were not announced. 
</P>
<P>
	Legler, a 10-year veteran, averaged 4.0 points and 1.3 rebounds  
in 30 games last season with Washington. 
</P>
<P>
	It is Legler's second stint with the Warriors as he appeared in  
24 games with them in 1994-95. 
</P>
<P>
	``Outside shooting was an area that we wanted to address this  
offseason, and we think that by adding Tim, who is one of the best 
3-point shooters in the league, we have filled a need on our 
basketball team,'' Warriors general manager Garry St. Jean said. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to Golden State and Washington, Legler has also  
played for Phoenix, Denver, Utah, Dallas and Washington. He also 
played six seasons in the Continental Basketball Association. 
</P>
<P>
	He has averaged 7.3 points, 1.6 rebounds and 1.3 assists over  
his career. In the 1995-96 season, he led the league with a .522 
percentage from 3-point range. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
